    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer375368863" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15851183118301806881">I really don&apos;t know what happened with Jeff Shaara from this book to his second attempt, <i>The Last Full Measure</i>, but I enjoyed this book more. There is still the rambling on, and the writing still has the same irritating problems, but not to the same extent as <i>Measure</i>. I still enjoy the historic events told in a comprehensible way; it fulfills my need to understand the order in which things happened. I must say, I could not read two pages where he goes on about the death of General Jackson, it is</span>
  <span id="freeText15851183118301806881" style="display:none">I really don't know what happened with Jeff Shaara from this book to his second attempt, <i>The Last Full Measure</i>, but I enjoyed this book more. There is still the rambling on, and the writing still has the same irritating problems, but not to the same extent as <i>Measure</i>. I still enjoy the historic events told in a comprehensible way; it fulfills my need to understand the order in which things happened. I must say, I could not read two pages where he goes on about the death of General Jackson, it is just too heart-wrenching. Even though I knew it was coming, I still was not able to read it. All in all, a much better read than his second novel. </span>
